{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"cfe98d94-f2b6-58e5-828a-449fb49d3b2e","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5f82f38d-6364-4bfc-b90e-7ff20e9fcb37 --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field 5f82f38d-6364-4bfc-b90e-7ff20e9fcb37 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item aec7cb48-c35f-4ae2-83b5-4d3d2e54f26e --><!-- begin field 8ca6b156-0ad6-4489-bfc7-af96ecff1a16 --><ul><li class=\"MsoNormal\">In the UK, the incidence of giant cell arteritis (GCA) is approximately 2.2 per 10,000 person years [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Lazarewicz, 2019</a>].<ul><li class=\"MsoNormal\">A full time GP is likely to see a new case every 1–2 years [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Barraclough, 2012</a>].</li></ul></li><li class=\"MsoNormal\">The incidence varies with age, ethnicity, and gender.<ul><li>Prevalence increases with age — GCA is rare before 50 years of age [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Hoffman, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Lazarewicz, 2019</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Mackie, 2020a</a>].<ul><li>A study using data from the UK Clinical Practice Research Datalink (n = 4671) found the highest incidence (7.4 per 10,000 person years) to be in women aged 70–79 years [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Petri, 2015</a>].</li></ul></li><li>GCA is most common in Scandinavian countries and in populations of Northern European descent [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Petri, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Turesson, 2019</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Mollan, 2020</a>].</li><li>It is 2–3 times more common in women than in men [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Ly, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Petri, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Hoffman, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Prior, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/giant-cell-arteritis/references/\">Lazarewicz, 2019</a>].</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 8ca6b156-0ad6-4489-bfc7-af96ecff1a16 --><!-- end item aec7cb48-c35f-4ae2-83b5-4d3d2e54f26e -->","topic":{"id":"7eefe727-da7a-5ac5-a30a-dadcb4a4de90","topicId":"922f2e2a-90b2-4d8e-8df9-97f686e2dd9c","topicName":"Giant cell arteritis","slug":"giant-cell-arteritis","lastRevised":"Last revised in September 2020","chapters":[{"id":"28844a63-ce71-58a4-ac10-fb8f990a2ace","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9ffc44fb-e6ab-5564-afaf-41f6ec23ae59","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"d9822672-70ac-5f30-a37c-163c926d69f9","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"8b641dad-e801-5f07-a15f-837c9e204ae5","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"b6663d8f-4d43-5493-b6ea-21be0eeae0f0","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id"